.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.300044906633116e-56, \"text\": \"Jesse Owens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\"}, {\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9878277524155576, \"rank\": 0.012322107594687827, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jewish athletes\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"the regime\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1098}, {\"ngram\": \"four gold medals\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"the party's race ideologies\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"consternation\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"the dictator\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1245}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The onset of World War II three years later made Berlin 1936 the last Olympics until 1948.\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1936_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Berlin 1936\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1936_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1936_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The onset\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"World War II\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1334}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The accommodation originally used to house athletes was then repurposed by the German army during the war, but the venues have been unused and unmaintained since then.\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1568, 