 \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"Herzegovina\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"nine new venues\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2044}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2085}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the venues were the Trebevi\\u0107 Bobsleigh and Luge Track, which was of particular note for being the fastest and steepest in the world at the time.\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trebevi\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.9466040856134769, \"rank\": 0.04021164021163416, \"text\": \"Trebevi\\u0107\", \"types\": [\"Q473972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trebevi\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trebevi\\u0107\"}, {\"begin\": 2123, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobsleigh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.305614115474418e-16, \"text\": \"Bobsleigh\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobsleigh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobsleigh\"}, {\"begin\": 2137, \"end\": 2141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.496317528111572e-21, \"text\": \"Luge\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the venues\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"particular note\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2177}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2225}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2237}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The track ran for 1,300 metres, with 30,000 spectators watching the bobsleigh events and 20,000 attending the luge.\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The track\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2249}, {\"ngram\": \"1,300 metres\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2270}, {\"ngram\": \"30,000 spectators\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"the bobsleigh events\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"the luge\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it took on a very different role when war broke out in the country just eight years later.\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a very different role\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Bosnian War, which engulfed the region from 1992 until 1995, following the break-up of the former Yugoslavia, saw most of the venues from the Winter Games destroyed.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2560, \"end\": 2570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yugoslavia\", \"score\": 0.7952814508601095, \"rank\": 0.2574164727634758, \"text\": \"Yugoslavia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yugoslavia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yugoslavia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Bosnian War\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2473}, {\"ngram\": \"the region\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2500}, {\"ngram\": \"the break-up\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"the venues\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2594}, {\"ngram\": \"the Winter Games\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2616}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bobsleigh track, meanwhile, became a concrete trench and artillery stronghold for Bosnian Serb forces, with defensive fighting holes drilled into the last stretch of track.\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2715, \"end\": 2727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs_of_Bosnia_and_Herzegovina\", \"score\": 0.9997585665782741, \"rank\": 0.00020624738271540633, \"text\": \"Bosnian Serb\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs_of_Bosnia_and_Herzegovina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs_of_Bosnia_and_Herzegovina\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bobsleigh track\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2648}, {\"ngram\": \"a concrete trench\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2685}, {\"ngram\": \"artillery stronghold\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"defensive fighting holes\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2765}, {\"ngram\": \"the last stretch\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 2799, \"to\": 2804}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the war, which claimed around 100,000 lives and saw Sarajevo shelled 329 times a day on average, the track fell into disuse and later became a target for graffiti.\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2869, \"end\": 2877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarajevo\", \"score\": 0.9987863367553239, \"rank\": 0.001215138013196119, \"text\": \"Sarajevo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarajevo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarajevo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2824}, {\"ngram\": \"around 100,000 lives\", \"from\": 2840, \"to\": 2860}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 2923}, {\"ngram\": \"disuse\", \"from\": 2934, \"to\": 2940}, {\"ngram\": \"a target\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 2966}, {\"ngram\": \"graffiti\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 2979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Restoration work on the track began in 2014, but plans for a full renovation were shelved in 2019 due to cost.\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 3092, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Restoration work\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 2998}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3011}, {\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3036}, {\"ngram\": \"a full renovation\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3058}, {\"ngram\": \"cost\", \"from\": 3087, \"to\": 3091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, a hotel built for Olympic visitors became a prison for Bosnian Muslims during the war.\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3160, \"end\": 3175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bosniaks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.248149558964493e-15, \"text\": \"Bosnian Muslims\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bosniaks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bosniaks\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a hotel\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3112}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic visitors\", \"from\": 3123, \"to\": 3139}, {\"ngram\": \"a prison\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3155}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On a more chilling note, a winners' podium from the Games became a place of execution for prisoners while the conflict was ongoing.\", \"from\": 3193, \"to\": 3324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a more chilling note\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3216}, {\"ngram\": \"a winners' podium\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3235}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 3241, \"to\": 3250}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3265}, {\"ngram\": \"execution\", \"from\": 3269, \"to\": 3278}, {\"ngram\": \"prisoners\", \"from\": 3283, \"to\": 3292}, {\"ngram\": \"the conflict\", \"from\": 3299, \"to\": 3311}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There had been some hope that venues such as the track might be restored as part of Barcelona's bid for the 2030 Winter Olympics, given that Sarajevo is twinned with the Spanish city.\", \"from\": 3326, \"to\": 3509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3410, \"end\": 3419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\", \"score\": 0.9999991432390776, \"rank\": 8.567614734568552e-07, \"text\": \"Barcelona\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\"}, {\"begin\": 3467, \"end\": 3475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarajevo\", \"