 \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heraklion\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Two decades later, very little remains\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3667}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\u00a38bn venue\", \"from\": 3701, \"to\": 3715}, {\"ngram\": \"host\", \"from\": 3729, \"to\": 3733}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2004 games\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3751}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The baseball and softball stadiums have been permanently shut, and are now overgrown with weeds and plants - with grass sprouting between the seats - while the kayak venue, the beach volleyball venue, and the training pools also sit unused.\", \"from\": 3754, \"to\": 3994, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The baseball and softball stadiums\", \"from\": 3754, \"to\": 3788}, {\"ngram\": \"weeds\", \"from\": 3844, \"to\": 3849}, {\"ngram\": \"plants\", \"from\": 3854, \"to\": 3860}, {\"ngram\": \"the seats\", \"from\": 3892, \"to\": 3901}, {\"ngram\": \"the kayak venue\", \"from\": 3910, \"to\": 3925}, {\"ngram\": \"the beach volleyball venue\", \"from\": 3927, \"to\": 3953}, {\"ngram\": \"the training pools\", \"from\": 3959, \"to\": 3977}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic village was built on the site of what used to be an airport, and the Greek government decided not to invest further in the complex following the country's financial crisis in 2009.\", \"from\": 3996, \"to\": 4188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4077, \"end\": 4082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999999879300959, \"rank\": 8.64059709864271e-09, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic village\", \"from\": 3996, \"to\": 4015}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 4029, \"to\": 4037}, {\"ngram\": \"an airport\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4067}, {\"ngram\": \"the complex\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4138}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's financial crisis\", \"from\": 4149, \"to\": 4179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, some of the venues have survived and are still used to day.\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the venues\", \"from\": 4207, \"to\": 4217}, {\"ngram\": \"day\", \"from\": 4254, \"to\": 4257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among them is the Ano Liosa Arena, which was converted into an arts and entertainment facility, and the OAKA area - home to the main Olympic Stadium - which has played host to concerts by the likes of Shakira and Madonna.\", \"from\": 4259, \"to\": 4480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4363, \"end\": 4367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\", \"score\": 0.9999857662372793, \"rank\": 1.4233965128766628e-05, \"text\": \"OAKA\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\"}, {\"begin\": 4460, \"end\": 4467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shakira\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.919091278595824e-29, \"text\": \"Shakira\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shakira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shakira\"}, {\"begin\": 4472, \"end\": 4479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madonna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.447341462730197e-41, \"text\": \"Madonna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madonna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madonna\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Ano Liosa Arena\", \"from\": 4273, \"to\": 4292}, {\"ngram\": \"an arts and entertainment facility\", \"from\": 4319, \"to\": 4353}, {\"ngram\": \"the main Olympic Stadium\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4407}, {\"ngram\": \"host\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4431}, {\"ngram\": \"concerts\", \"from\": 4435, \"to\": 4443}, {\"ngram\": \"the likes\", \"from\": 4447, \"to\": 4456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the 2006 Winter Olympics in Turin, Italy, around \\u00a34.4 billion was spent on bringing the best games possible to the city, with many of the venues constructed against the breathtaking backdrops of the Alps.\", \"from\": 4482, \"to\": 4690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4514, \"end\": 4519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.781488723394016e-15, \"text\": \"Turin\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\"}, {\"begin\": 4521, \"end\": 4526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.8765113999935656, \"rank\": 0.1408863056606499, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2006 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 4486, \"to\": 4510}, {\"ngram\": \"the best games\", \"from\": 4570, \"to\": 4584}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 4597, \"to\": 4605}, {\"ngram\": \"the venues\", \"from\": 4620, \"to\": 4630}, {\"ngram\": \"the breathtaking backdrops\", \"from\": 4651, \"to\": 4677}, {\"ngram\": \"the Alps\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"18 years on, however, and little remains of the venues, which were abandoned and left to the elements and are now rusting and covered in weeds.\", \"from\": 4692, \"to\": 4835, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"little remains\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4732}, {\"ngram\": \"the venues\", \"from\": 4736, \"to\": 4746}, {\"ngram\": \"the elements\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4793}, {\"ngram\": \"weeds\", \"from\": 4829, \"to\": 4834}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The village, meanwhile, was taken over by refugees and migrants from over 30 different countries including Libya and Somalia.\", \"from\": 4837, \"to\": 4962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4944, \"end\": 4949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Libya\", \"score\": 0.9999996318852704, \"rank\": 3.58339229544001e-07, \"text\": \"Libya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Libya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Libya\"}, {\"begin\": 4954, \"end\": 4961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Somalia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999809006, \"rank\": 1.2318404712258491e-11, \"text\": \"Somalia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Somalia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Somalia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The village\", \"from\": 4837, \"to\": 4848}, {\"ngram\": \"refugees\", \"from\": 4879, \"to\": 4887}, {\"ngram\": \"migrants\", \"from\": 4892, \"to\": 4900}, {\"ngram\": \"over 30 different countries\", \"from\": 4906, \"to\": 4933}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Guardianreported that over 1,100 people were living in the former village in 2016 - although they were evicted by the authorities three years later.\", \"from\": 4964, \"to\": 5116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Guardianreported\", \"from\": 4964, \"to\": 4984}, {\"ngram\": \"over 1,100 people\", \"from\": 4990, \"to\": 5007}, {\"ngram\": \"the former village\", \"from\": 5023, \"to\": 5041}, {\"ngram\": \"the authorities\", \"from\": 5082, \"to\": 5097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The site has now been converted into student accommodation and social housing for up to 400 people.\", \"from\": 5118, \"to\": 5217, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The site\", \"from\": 5118, \"to\": 5126}, {\"ngram\": \"student accommodation\", \"from\": 5155, \"to\": 5176}, {\"ngram\": \"social housing\", \"from\": 5181, \"to\": 5195}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 400 people\", \"from\": 5200, \"to\": 5216}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Few of the venues used at the Beijing games in 2008 remained in use after the event, despite China spending an eye-watering \\u00a332bn on infrastructure.\", \"from\": 5219, \"to\": 5367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5249, \"end\": 5256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8790892840570829, \"rank\": 0.13754088251960792, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5312, \"end\": 5317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999985966497, \"rank\": 1.2347382429206406e-09, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the venues\", \"from\": 5226, \"to\": 5236}, {\"ngram\": \"use\", \"from\": 5283, \"to\": 5286}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 5293, \"to\": 5302}, {\"ngram\": \"an eye-watering\", \"from\": 5327, \"to\": 5342}, {\"ngram\": \"infrastructure\", \"from\": 5352, \"to\": 5366}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as race tracks and the BMX circuit being overrun with greenery, the whitewater rafting venue has been abandoned, while the beach volleyball arena has begun to rust and rot.\", \"from\": 5369, \"to\": 5549, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5400, \"end\": 5403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999999986443981, \"rank\": 1.3555954883309147e-09, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"race tracks\", \"from\": 5380, \"to\": 5391}, {\"ngram\": \"greenery\", \"from\": 5431, \"to\": 5439}, {\"ngram\": \"the whitewater rafting venue\", \"from\": 5441, \"to\": 5469}, {\"ngram\": \"the beach volleyball arena\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5522}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps saddest of all is the demise of Olympic mascots Nini, Yingjing and Beibei, who have been left lying across the former Olympic village, surrounded by weeds.\", \"from\": 5551, \"to\": 5714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5626, \"end\": 5632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beibei_District\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beibei\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beibei_District\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beibei_District\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the demise\", \"from\": 5577, \"to\": 5587}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic mascots Nini\", \"from\": 5591, \"to\": 5611}, {\"ngram\": \"Yingjing\", \"from\": 5613, \"to\": 5621}, {\"ngram\": \"the former Olympic village\", \"from\": 5666, \"to\": 5692}, {\"ngram\": \"weeds\", \"from\": 5708, \"to\": 5713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only the Beijing National Stadium - known as the 'Bird's Nest' due to its intricate design - has survived, going on to host concerts and sporting events as well as the opening and closing ceremonies of the 2022 Winter Olympics and Winter Paralympics.\", \"from\": 5716, \"to\": 5966, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 'Bird's Nest\", \"from\": 5761, \"to\": 5777}, {\"ngram\": \"its intricate design\", \"from\": 5786, \"to\": 5806}, {\"ngram\": \"host concerts\", \"from\": 5835, \"to\": 5848}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting events\", \"from\": 5853, \"to\": 5868}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening and closing ceremonies\", \"from\": 5880, \"to\": 5914}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2022 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 5918, \"to\": 5942}, {\"ngram\": \"Winter Paralympics\", \"from\": 5947, \"to\": 5965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The venues built for the 2016 Olympics in Rio began falling into disrepair just six months after the games ended.\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 6081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6010, \"end\": 6013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9396758900724764, \"rank\": 0.06419671991692052, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The venues\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 5978}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2016 Olympics\", \"from\": 5989, \"to\": 6006}, {\"ngram\": \"disrepair\", \"from\": 6033, \"to\": 6042}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 6065, \"to\": 6074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Arena Carioca has lived on to become part of the country's Olympic training centre, and hosted the Pan American Gymnastics championships in 2022, others have been left to decay - despite the Games costing the Brazilian government \\u00a330bn to construct.\", \"from\": 6083, \"to\": 6342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6192, \"end\": 6229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Gymnastics_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pan American Gymnastics championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Gymnastics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Gymnastics_Championships\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Arena Carioca\", \"from\": 6089, \"to\": 6106}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 6130, \"to\": 6134}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's Olympic training centre\", \"from\": 6138, \"to\": 6175}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 6239, \"to\": 6245}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6280, \"to\": 6289}, {\"ngram\": \"the Brazilian government\", \"from\": 6298, \"to\": 6322}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00a330bn\", \"from\": 6323, \"to\": 6328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The famous Maracana Stadium, which hosted the opening and closing ceremonies, also suffered from vandalism and neglect, only returning to its former glory after being taken over by new management.\", \"from\": 6344, \"to\": 6540, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The famous Maracana Stadium\", \"from\": 6344, \"to\": 6371}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening and closing ceremonies\", \"from\": 6386, \"to\": 6420}, {\"ngram\": \"vandalism\", \"from\": 6441, \"to\": 6450}, {\"ngram\": \"neglect\", \"from\": 6455, \"to\": 6462}, {\"ngram\": \"its former glory\", \"from\": 6482, \"to\": 6498}, {\"ngram\": \"new management\", \"from\": 6525, \"to\": 6539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the saddest story of all concerns the Aquatics Centre, which cost nearly \\u00a330 million to build but was closed by a judge amid safety concerns over stagnated water at the facility.\", \"from\": 6542, \"to\": 6728, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Perhaps the saddest story\", \"from\": 6542, \"to\": 6567}, {\"ngram\": \"all concerns\", \"from\": 6571, \"to\": 6583}, {\"ngram\": \"the Aquatics Centre\", \"from\": 6584, \"to\": 6603}, {\"ngram\": \"a judge\", \"from\": 6662, \"to\": 6669}, {\"ngram\": \"safety concerns\", \"from\": 6675, \"to\": 6690}, {\"ngram\": \"stagnated water\", \"from\": 6696, \"to\": 6711}, {\"ngram\": \"the facility\", \"from\": 6715, \"to\": 6727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was highlighted as a potential breeding ground for dengue fever as well as mosquitoes carrying the Zika virus, which struck Brazil shortly before the Games in 2016.\", \"from\": 6730, \"to\": 6897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6857, \"end\": 6863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9999796972434647, \"rank\": 2.0303168795276552e-05, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a potential breeding ground\", \"from\": 6752, \"to\": 6779}, {\"ngram\": \"dengue fever\", \"from\": 6784, \"to\": 6796}, {\"ngram\": \"mosquitoes\", \"from\": 6808, \"to\": 6818}, {\"ngram\": \"the Zika virus\", \"from\": 6828, \"to\": 6842}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6879, \"to\": 6888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, it still lies unused.\", \"from\": 6898, \"to\": 6926, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Olympic cyclist forced to dash into rowdy pub for toilet break mid-race ArrowMORE:Simone Biles fumes at Olympic crowd after missing out on medal ArrowMORE:How much the hammer throw, s